    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1e9409c2_e56be1ea",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/context.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 82,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109829
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-03T21:30:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "What\u0027s the point of this? Why not just update \"c\"?\n\nTraditionally, the reason we would leave original \"c\" around is so we could return it in the error case, e.g., \"return c, err\". This stabilizes misuse cases:\n\nc, err :\u003d doSomething(c)\nif err !\u003d nil {\n  logging.Errorf(c, \"FAILED!\") // Broken if \"c\" is returned as nil in error cases.\n  return err\n}\n\n---\n\nThis is why, for some functions, we actually pass \"c\" by reference and update it on success; that way, there\u0027s no failed expectation of \"c\"\u0027s validity. This is a method that I preferred, and I\u0027d recommend that you use it here:\n\nfunc WithAccess(c *context.Context, ...) {\n  nc :\u003d *c\n  ...\n  if err :\u003d WithProjectNamespace(\u0026nc, ...)\n  if err :\u003d datastore.Get(nc, ...)\n\n  // (On success, update reference)\n  *c \u003d nc\n  return nil\n}\n\nAlternatively, you can make sure you return original \"c\" in your error-case returns. Your choice.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 82,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 82,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "af60ac12d61b409eee25b77f4f60d806d775d02a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "715ba887_32191655",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/context.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 82,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-04T18:45:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Makes sense. I didn\u0027t know that. But you\u0027re right that would\u0027ve been a bug.\n\nI\u0027m not super attached to one way or another, but I want to keep this as consistent as possible with the rest of luci-go, which is why I picked to use a pass-by-value context.",
      "parentUuid": "1e9409c2_e56be1ea",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 82,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 82,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "af60ac12d61b409eee25b77f4f60d806d775d02a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
