      "writtenOn": "2018-05-04T18:45:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s true that LogStream is initialized and calculated twice.  I did it this way because otherwise the function signature would get super confusing (okay some of these are inputs, but this one is actually an output?  Which direction does data go??\n\nBut the same thing can be achieved in a simpler way by making LogStream an output of this function.\n\nIt does make the signature kind of long, but I think it would make it easier to follow.",
      "parentUuid": "d6f9d451_748e4589",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 88,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 88,
        "endChar": 38
