        "id": 1003190
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-03T18:05:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I notice this way of logging is done elsewhere in logdog code, and I think it looks nice. I guess the fields get attached to the app engine log entry, but not necessarily embedded in the log text?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 87,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 90,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "af60ac12d61b409eee25b77f4f60d806d775d02a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6d7851d3_930b03f6",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 90,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109829
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-03T21:30:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sort of - the logging system is formatted-message-plus-fields, borrowed from Logrus. In GAE, the tags are output as part of the log message, so the gain is (ATM) pretty low:\n\nLog Message :: {\"err\": \"some error\"}\n\nHowever, keeping them separate enables a cleaner logging message and offers the possibility of putting them in a better place if such an opportunity arose. Now that you mention it, before LogDog moved to Flex, we were going through the GAE logging API, which is text-only, but now that we\u0027re in Flex we can actually output the logs better, e.g., in User Labels or some other place:\n\nhttps://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/luci/gae/+/master/impl/cloud/logger.go\n\nI was hastily implementing \"logging.go\", so I forgot that this was an option, but it would be a really good idea to do.",
      "parentUuid": "85ddee70_966b36f4",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 87,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 90,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "af60ac12d61b409eee25b77f4f60d806d775d02a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6b9db843_e39a7134",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 90,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-04T18:45:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah in GKE we actually pass the log straight to fluentd via the JSON format (Where fields are first class and machine readable), and this shows up as structured data in Stackdriver!  eg you can filter/search on these fields or bubble them up as faucets.\n\nIn flex this gives us the option of using the stackdriver logging api to get structured logs.",
      "parentUuid": "6d7851d3_930b03f6",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 87,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 90,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "af60ac12d61b409eee25b77f4f60d806d775d02a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "597fc80e_fe669d88",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 90,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003190
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-04T20:01:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Neat, so using Fields/WithError is the recommended way of logging in general for Go code that uses go.chromium.org/luci/common/logging, including plain old GAE apps, right?",
      "parentUuid": "6b9db843_e39a7134",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 87,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 90,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "af60ac12d61b409eee25b77f4f60d806d775d02a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a9cd343c_2672cfa4",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 90,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109829
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-04T23:03:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, writing logging using fields lets the environment processing the logs decide what to do with the structured data. May be text dumping, may be something better, but expressing it is the first step.\n\nIt\u0027d be a fun project to do something more useful than text inlining with some for Logger implementations that allow this. If you\u0027d like to get more familiar with this package, I\u0027d be happy to support.",
      "parentUuid": "597fc80e_fe669d88",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 87,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 90,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "af60ac12d61b409eee25b77f4f60d806d775d02a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "78ce4be1_201f23b1",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 90,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-10T23:45:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Correct, assuming you have errors or bits of structured data you want to log.\n\nI think we\u0027ve been pretty consistent about using .WithError() since it\u0027s straightforward.  I don\u0027t think we use fields quite as often but I think adoption would increase if the benefits were clear (ie they show up in structured logging).",
      "parentUuid": "597fc80e_fe669d88",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 87,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 90,
        "endChar": 2
      },
