      "writtenOn": "2018-05-03T21:30:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You should have a special provision here for \"not found\". Like, if the user asks for a non-existent log, this will reflect as a datastore miss. More specifically, this will be a MultiError (b/c two parameters) with at least one miss in it. You\u0027ll want to return 404 for this.\n\nSee \"isNoSuchEntity\", used by \"get.go\": https://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/luci/luci-go/+/32cba3ac2ed647858e5fbdd7c2b05642c9c6745b/logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/util.go#46",
