      },
      "lineNbr": 114,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109829
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-03T21:30:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Previous comment: Please note in comment that \"fetch\" will close \"st\" on completion, or close it explicitly here:\n\ngo func() {\n  defer st.Close()\n  fetch(...)\n}\n\nI prefer this b/c the resource is destroyed in the same function as it\u0027s created, but either will do.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 114,
