      },
      "lineNbr": 232,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109829
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-03T21:30:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think we should forward verbatim internal error messages to the user. This could include any amount of data from any of the underlying layers. I don\u0027t know a good way to control for this, so I\u0027d prefer to just avoid doing it altogether.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 232,
        "startChar": 25,
        "endLine": 232,
        "endChar": 36
      },
      "revId": "af60ac12d61b409eee25b77f4f60d806d775d02a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "84d434be_46ad3bc2",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 232,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-04T18:45:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "From what I could see in the what I\u0027ve read, if we\u0027re explicitly passing in anything that isn\u0027t an Internal error, that\u0027s a pretty clear signal that the author intended the error to surface back up through the layers to the user.  This is why I made internal errors opaque but print everything else.",
      "parentUuid": "02d7a4e4_54f63d91",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 232,
        "startChar": 25,
        "endLine": 232,
        "endChar": 36
      },
      "revId": "af60ac12d61b409eee25b77f4f60d806d775d02a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "46d25074_76e3788f",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 232,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109829
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-04T23:03:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "There are a lot of call sites that don\u0027t use InternalReason, either b/c they were implemented before it was created or because they are third-party libraries (e.g., BigTable, GCS, etc.) and don\u0027t understand our error uage. A Storage implementation error, for example, would be forwarded directly here. I think this is something that you need to address, and should not be visible to the user.\n\nI see in your new code that you only show the text for non-internal errors.",
      "parentUuid": "84d434be_46ad3bc2",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 232,
        "startChar": 25,
        "endLine": 232,
        "endChar": 36
      },
      "revId": "af60ac12d61b409eee25b77f4f60d806d775d02a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c5197bf8_18975e49",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 232,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-10T23:45:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, new code _only_ shows text for errors that have been tagged with a grpc code.\n\nNon-tagged errors (which show up as grpc.Internal, for all intents and purposes) or errors with grpc.Internal are logged and a generic error is displayed.\n\nI think this probably makes sense?",
