      "writtenOn": "2018-05-03T21:30:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You might want to add a \"defer flusher.Flush\" just to squeeze out the last of anything in case there\u0027s an error before we fall back to standard HTTP handler.\n\nNote that one flush per LogEntry may be pretty aggressive; some log streams have millions of them. Perhaps you should only force a flush prior to retrying? This could be done as follows:\n\n1) Specify that if logResp.log and logResp.err are both nil, it is a signal that you are sleeping pending more logs.\n2) Have this react to that signal by flushing and continuing.",
      "range": {
